Trees sequester carbon, capturing CO2 as they grow and storing it as carbon, they create habitats for our wild-life, they transpire, they form clouds and rain, provide shelter and habitat for biodiversity.

With the holiday season just around the corner ‚Äî @treedom_trees are the sustainable gift that gives back ‚Äì to both the planet and to communities around the world. The trees are planted in sustainable agroforestry systems ‚Äì so not only will your trees offset carbon emissions, stop soil erosion, encourage reforestation and protect biodiversity, but they will also bring food security and revenue to smallholder farmers. All of @treedom_trees are geolocated & photographed, so you will receive updates on your tree and the project in which it is planted. ü•∞

There are days when I feel completely lost, unsure and self conscious. It‚Äôs hard not to assume things about someone‚Äôs life when you look at their best moments or this ‚Äúhighlight reel‚Äù here on Instagram. So I try and always remember we are all real human-beings all going through something, which unfortunately this platform forgets to focus on. I often receive messages & emails from you guys saying I wish I had your life or my dream is to be like you and you have inspired me to do so on ‚Äî But the hard reality is you don‚Äôt really know who I am or what I am actually doing. I try and always be transparent but the truth is I‚Äôve always been a private person and keep a lot of my personal life away from this platform. I‚Äôm shy & always felt like the outcast & never feel truly understood. So I initially used this space as a way to escape and curate a little world of my own. This still is the way I choose to share the world and this may be far from reality ‚Äî but this form of escapism and self expression has help me in many ways, definitely creatively but also mentally. It‚Äôs helped me to discover who I am & find my purpose. -

I‚Äôm not even sure why I‚Äôm writing this, but if you are reading this. Thank you, thank you for your support over the years, watching me grow and navigate this crazy thing we call life. Thank you for understanding humans are vulnerable & we are all going through something...‚ù§Ô∏è
